External Ingress Traffic

Traffic is routed from outside the cluster into the applications via F5 BigIP with TCP pass-through to the infrastructure nodes.  The infrastructure nodes run redundant ipfailover and haproxy prods which use hostname headers to route http/https traffic to the appropriate pod.

Egress Traffic

Traffic leaving a running pod destined outside of the cluster is first forwarded to its default gateway.  The gateway is the tun0 interface of the node currently running the pod.  A source NAT (SNAT) is performed to transform the source IP to that of the primary interface of the node where the pod is running.  The external system being accessed will see the Node IP as the source IP for all traffic.

• Source IP from any pod will look like any node in the cluster. 
  • All pods match this rule. 
  • Pods can can connect to the DB HOST on port 3306
